results.name: Decimal expansion of the volume of a dodecahedron with each edge of unit length.
comment: Equals 5*phi^3/(2*xi^2), phi being the golden ratio (A001622) and xi its associate (A182007). - _Stanislav Sykora_, Nov 23 2013
link: Ivan Panchenko, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
formula: Equals (sqrt(5)/2)*(phi)^4, where phi is the golden ratio. - _G. C. Greubel_, Jul 06 2017
xref: Cf. A001622 (phi), A182007 (phi associate), A020829 (regular tetrahedron volume), A131594 (regular octahedron volume), A102208 (regular icosahedron volume).
results.author: Bryan Jacobs (bryanjj(AT)gmail.com), Feb 10 2005
